As the business sets up discount for SMSF administration fee as a percentage| the spcd_offset_val_type_id will be 9. The details of the code is available in Btfg$cost_ovr_type (cached table)  ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME 9 spcd_perc_disc SPCD_PERC_DISC Discount in %  Appendix A (Avaloq Fee Concept) provides an explanation of how the special condition codes work. It is intended for general knowledge only. The steps describe below has already taken into account how the business intends to use the system and is sufficient for the current UI build.  Use the following steps to calculate the SMSF administration fee net of discount. 1. For each btfg_book_kind_id (i.e. component) of the SMSF administration fee where spcd_offset_val_type_id is equal to 9| calculate net fee amount of the component = tariff_amt * (1   (spcd_offset_val / 100)) 2. The net fee amount of each component (i.e. each of the amount calculated in first step) of SMSF administration fee  is rounded up to 2 decimal places. 3. Sum up the amount calculated in second step  Btfg$book_kind (cached table) for SMSF administration fee are provided below. This is for information only. The UI should not worry about what btfg_book_kind_id is. Source Entity Name: BP FEE SCHEDULE - PORTFOLIO MANAGEMENT FEE
BP FEE SCHEDULE - PORTFOLIO MANAGEMENT FEE
Transformation_Mapping rule: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.          For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.          In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.          In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

Target Entity Name: VISUAL MAP - BP FEE SCHEDULE - INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT FEES
VISUAL MAP - BP FEE SCHEDULE - INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT FEES
Transformation_Mapping rule: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.     For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.     In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.     In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.
Lower dollar boundary for a tier in a sliding fee component   Eg. 0
Upper dollar boundary for a tier in a sliding fee component   Eg. 110

Target Entity Name: BP FEE SCHEDULE - PORTFOLIO MANAGEMENT FEE
BP FEE SCHEDULE - PORTFOLIO MANAGEMENT FEE
Transformation_Mapping rule: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.          For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.          In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.          In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

Transformation_Mapping rule: As the business sets up discount for SMSF administration fee as a percentage| the spcd_offset_val_type_id will be 9. The details of the code is available in Btfg$cost_ovr_type (cached table)          ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME     9 spcd_perc_disc SPCD_PERC_DISC Discount in %          Appendix A (Avaloq Fee Concept) provides an explanation of how the special condition codes work. It is intended for general knowledge only. The steps describe below has already taken into account how the business intends to use the system and is sufficient for the current UI build.          Use the following steps to calculate the SMSF administration fee net of discount.     1. For each btfg_book_kind_id (i.e. component) of the SMSF administration fee where spcd_offset_val_type_id is equal to 9| calculate net fee amount of the component = tariff_amt * (1   (spcd_offset_val / 100))     2. The net fee amount of each component (i.e. each of the amount calculated in first step) of SMSF administration fee  is rounded up to 2 decimal places.     3. Sum up the amount calculated in second step          Btfg$book_kind (cached table) for SMSF administration fee are provided below. This is for information only. The UI should not worry about what btfg_book_kind_id is.          ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME     544 btfg$smsf_fd_admin_fee SMSF_FD_ADMIN_FEE SMSF Administration fee     555 btfg$smsf_fd_admin_fee_dg SMSF_FD_ADMIN_FEE_DG SMSF Administration fee DG

Transformation_Mapping rule: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.     For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.     In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.     In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.
